cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with visual localization and mapping using convolutional neural networks for dynamic object detection. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper addresses challenges in mobile robotics and proposes a solution to improve the robustness of vision-based localization in crowded environments. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper uses a semi-supervised learning approach to train the neural network model. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper proposes an AI-based solution to address the problem of dynamic object detection in visual localization. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category as the paper deals with processing visual data to improve localization and mapping in dynamic environments.
